      "description": "This is a good, honest car that presents well and should make a solid driver for someone who wants something enjoyable and usable without paying premium money for a top-tier show example. It appears to have been cared for properly, with the kind of overall condition you\u2019d expect from a well-kept car that has been maintained and enjoyed rather than hidden away. Inside and out, it should show nicely, but buyers should expect a good driver-quality vehicle rather than a flawless, concours-level car. Overall, it\u2019s the kind of car you can feel good about owning, driving, and improving over time if desired.",
